I

InsightsCallback<T> - Class in com.amazon.insights
The InsightsCallback is the callback object that you can set on an InsightsHandler via InsightsHandler.setCallback(InsightsCallback) to react upon success or failure of the associated asynchronous method.
InsightsCallback() - Constructor for class com.amazon.insights.InsightsCallback
 
InsightsCredentials - Interface in com.amazon.insights
The InsightsCredentials interface is implemented by all classes that can provide identification of the application and keys for signing/encrypting data within the SDK.
InsightsError - Interface in com.amazon.insights.error
InsightsError is the interface implemented by all error classes that can be returned by the API.
It can be used to get a human-readable format containing details of the error.
Note that the default behavior of the InsightsCallback class which can be used to retrieve the error, is to log the message string to the Android log.
InsightsHandler<T> - Interface in com.amazon.insights
InsightsHandler is a handle to any asynchronous long-running operation, such as ABTestClient.getVariations(String...), which allows you to assign a callback that is notified on completion (whether successful or not) of the operation.
InsightsOptions - Interface in com.amazon.insights
The InsightsOptions interface is implemented by all classes that can provide options such as enablement of event collection and allowance of event delivery on WAN within the SDK.
InvalidArgumentError - Class in com.amazon.insights.error
InvalidArgumentError indicates when an invalid argument is passed to a method
It can be used to get a human-readable format of the error as well as the argument name that was invalid.
Note that the default behavior of the InsightsCallback class which can be used to retrieve the error, is to log the message string which will include the name of the invalid argument to the Android log.
InvalidArgumentError(String, String, String) - Constructor for class com.amazon.insights.error.InvalidArgumentError

NullArgumentError - Class in com.amazon.insights.error
NullArgumentError indicates when a null argument is passed to a method which can not be null
It can be used to get the human-readable format of the details of the error as well as the argument name that was null.
Note that the default behavior of the InsightsCallback class which can be used to retrieve the error, is to log the message string which will include the name of the invalid argument to the Android log.

UnexpectedError - Class in com.amazon.insights.error
UnexpectedError indicates when an unexpected error occurs in the SDK
It can be used to get the human-readable format of the details of the error as well as the exception object that is related to the error
Note that the default behavior of the InsightsCallback class which can be used to retrieve the error, is to log the message string to the Android log.
